    "title": "从动荡走向规范",
    "page_range": "31-32",
    "summary": "**Topics:** 2025 mobile game user acquisition (UA) market trends, advertising expenditure dynamics, marketing strategy evolution, quarterly performance analysis, ROI optimization versus scale expansion.\n**Entities:** Mobile game advertisers/marketers, Singular (data provider/report publisher), high-download game categories.\n**Dates/Timeframes:** Full year 2025, Q1–Q4 2025, holiday season (Q4).\n**Definitions/Concepts:** Market transition from a prolonged \"emergency state\" to \"self-discipline and standardization\"; \"rational growth path\" prioritizing sustainable value extraction from incremental spend over blind expansion.\n**Procedures/Strategies:** Cautious budget allocation, efficiency-focused testing and validation, real-time operations, iterative content and creative optimization, implementation of mature creative workflows and clear measurement systems.\n**Claims:** The 2025 UA market stabilized with low single-digit YoY ad spend growth, reflecting restored industry confidence without reckless expansion. Q1 installs declined MoM due to an efficiency-first focus; Q2 showed early recovery signs; Q3 saw significant install rebounds (mid-to-high single-digit to low double-digit MoM growth for top categories). Q4 broke historical trends: increased holiday budgets maintained or slightly improved ROI despite higher bidding pressure, ending the industry norm of sacrificing returns for peak-season scale.\n**Tables/Figures/Metrics:** References a figure titled \"2025年游戏获客：真实变革何在\" (2025 Game UA: Where is the Real Change?) sourced from the Singular 2025 Quarterly Trend Report. Key metrics include YoY ad spend growth (low single-digit), quarterly MoM install fluctuations, Q4 ROI stability/improvement, and competitive bidding pressure levels.\n**Evidence Types:** Quarterly trend analy..."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0048",
    "title": "2025 年移动游戏发展势头：起步缓慢，强劲收尾增长回归，但态势温和且不均衡",
    "page_range": "32-33",
    "summary": "**可检索问题映射摘要：**\n- **主题 (Topics)：** 2025年移动游戏市场增长节奏、各品类下载量与营收格局演变、买量策略从“下载量导向”向“价值导向”的转型。\n- **实体 (Entities)：** Singular（数据报告机构）、移动游戏品类（休闲、混合休闲、中核、策略类）、广告主/发行团队。\n- **时间/日期 (Dates)：** 2025年全年；重点聚焦2025年第三、四季度（Q3-Q4）。\n- **定义/概念 (Definitions)：** 以价值为核心的优化方法论（指基于早期价值信号，将创意策略、竞价模型与渠道组合全面对齐用户付费倾向，而非单纯追逐下载量的策略框架）。\n- **流程/策略 (Procedures)：** 追踪早期价值信号；将优化目标从下载量转向用户付费倾向；整合创意、竞价与渠道策略以匹配高价值用户路径。\n- **核心主张/结论 (Claims)：** 休闲与混合休闲游戏占据下载量主导；中核与策略类游戏为营收主力，虽单次安装成本（CPI）高出30%-50%，但凭借更高付费转化率与用户终身价值（LTV）实现超额回报；价值导向优化在2025年加速普及，尤其在Q3-Q4有效对冲行业成本上涨，实现规模与可持续增长的平衡。\n- **指标/数据 (Metrics)：** 中核/策略类游戏CPI高出30%至50%；付费转化率与LTV显著提升；Q3-Q4增长表现突出。\n- **证据类型 (Evidence Types)：** 第三方行业季度趋势报告数据（Singular 2025年季度趋势报告H2 Rebond）；市场格局与策略效果的实证分析。\n- **图表/表格 (Tables/Figures)：** 本节文本未直接展示具体图表，但明确引用Singular季度报告作为底层数据支撑。"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0049",
    "title": "不同游戏品类的规模和盈利模式各不相同 各游戏品类的规模与变现继续分化",
    "page_range": "33-34",
    "summary": "**Topics:** Game user acquisition (UA) market trends, seasonal marketing patterns, ad spend efficiency, genre scale & monetization divergence.\n**Entities:** Singular (report publisher/data source), game marketing/UA sector.\n**Dates/Timeframes:** 2025 (full year), Q1, Q2, Q3, Q4, holiday season.\n**Key Claims & Trends:** Seasonal UA fluctuations in 2025 became more predictable; Q1 focused on cautious optimization; Q2 shifted to expansion despite limited install growth; Q3 sustained quarter-over-quarter increases in installs and ad spend; Q4 holiday ad spend surged without the typical ROAS decline; the 2025 market is defined by precise, measured growth rather than contraction.\n**Strategic Procedures/Implications:** Success relies on operational readiness for peak periods rather than avoiding high-cost cycles; requires a strategic shift from optimization to targeted expansion across quarters.\n**Metrics & Indicators:** Install volume, marketing/ad spend, ROAS (advertising ROI), seasonal predictability, quarter-over-quarter growth rates.\n**Evidence Type & Source:** Quarterly industry trend analysis; data sourced from the \"Singular 2025 Quarterly Trends Report\" (www.singular.net).\n**Tables/Figures:** None explicitly detailed in the text; underlying data attributed to the cited Singular quarterly report.\n**Retrieval Questions Answered:** What were the quarterly game UA trends in 2025? How did seasonal factors impact game marketing spend and ROAS in 2025? What strategies defined successful game user acquisition in 2025? How did holiday season ad performance differ from previous years? What metrics characterize the 2025 game marketing landscape? How do game genre scale and monetization models compare/diverge? (per section title)"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0050",
    "title": "市场周期性规律日益清晰，且更具落地价值",
    "page_range": "34-35",
    "summary": "This section addresses questions regarding global mobile platform dynamics and the evolution of cross-platform marketing strategies.\n- **Topics/Questions Answered:** How do Android and iOS compare in market performance and user acquisition? How are top brands adapting their marketing strategies for different mobile platforms?\n- **Entities:** Android, iOS, global mobile market, top brands/marketers.\n- **Metrics:** Android’s average user acquisition cost is typically 40%–60% lower than iOS. Android leads in total install volume; iOS generates disproportionately high revenue relative to its install count.\n- **Claims:** The global mobile platform landscape remains stable. Android drives volume through device scale, broad geographic coverage, and lower costs. iOS serves as a high-efficiency monetization channel. Marketing optimization has shifted from a unified approach to platform-specific strategies.\n- **Procedures/Strategies:** Treating Android and iOS as distinct acquisition environments; customizing creative assets, bidding strategies, and performance evaluation systems for each platform.\n- **Dates:** None specified.\n- **Definitions:** None explicitly provided.\n- **Tables/Figures:** None referenced.\n- **Evidence Types:** Industry market analysis, comparative platform metrics, strategic observation."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0051",
    "title": "2025年广告预算流向解析",
    "page_range": "35",
    "summary": "本章节（2025年广告预算流向解析）系统解析了2025年数字广告预算分配与投放优化策略。**主题**涵盖游戏买量渠道差异化定位、付费社交平台市场地位、渠道多元化战略演进及创意性能优化。**实体**包括Android、iOS、付费社交平台（Paid Social）及多平台数字广告主。**日期/周期**聚焦2025年全年，重点追踪下半年（H2）、Q3与Q4趋势。**核心主张**指出：付费社交仍是游戏获客核心支柱但集中度风险加剧；渠道多元化已从增长选项升级为风险管理的必然要求；创意是全渠道最可控的业绩驱动因素，短视频与UGC风格素材持续优于静态/过度包装内容，且创意迭代速度直接决定ROAS衰减周期，Q4慢速刷新将显著拖累收益。**指标**涵盖广告支出占比、安装量贡献、边际收益趋势、ROAS及多元化广告主较单一渠道高出的中个位数百分比差异。**定义**明确界定了“渠道过度集中”风险、渠道多元化战略路径，以及创意迭代速度、更新周期与内容格式分类（短视频、UGC启发式、静态）。**流程/策略**建议广告主采用多元分散布局，并建立以快速创意测试、UGC素材应用及高频率刷新为核心的工作流以对冲竞价波动与创意疲劳。**图表与证据类型**引用“2025年广告预算流向解析”数据可视化图表（未提及具体表格），结论基于Singular 2025年季度趋势报告的季度追踪数据、广告主分组对比分析及定性行业论述。"
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0055",
    "title": "成熟的衡量能力，铸就竞争优势",
    "page_range": "38-39",
    "summary": "This section addresses retrieval queries regarding advertising measurement maturity, attribution modeling, and privacy-driven signal mitigation in 2025. It answers questions across the following dimensions:\n• **Topics & Claims:** How refined measurement capabilities determine corporate expansion vs. stagnation; why advanced attribution frameworks enable decisive budget allocation and clearer optimization while simple models fail; how last-click attribution undervalues top/mid-funnel activities; how multi-touch attribution reveals assist value and cross-channel impact to balance media strategies and protect long-term growth; and how leading advertisers successfully navigate persistent iOS privacy signal loss.\n• **Entities & Dates:** 2025; Singular (publisher); iOS platform; game advertisers; leading/top enterprises.\n• **Definitions & Concepts:** Last-Click Attribution, Multi-Touch Attribution (MTA), Assist Value, Cross-Channel Impact, Modeled Conversions, Hybrid Performance Metrics, Signal Loss.\n• **Procedures & Practices:** Allocating budgets using advanced attribution frameworks; adopting MTA to evaluate full-funnel value; deploying modeled conversions and hybrid metrics to maintain optimization continuity; aligning internal stakeholders around modeled outputs to reduce friction and accelerate decision-making.\n• **Metrics & Indicators:** Performance signals, assist value, cross-channel impact, modeled conversion outputs, hybrid performance indicators.\n• **Evidence Types:** Industry trend data from the Singular 2025 Quarterly Trends Report; observational analysis of advertiser adaptation to privacy constraints and market complexity.\n• **Tables & Figures:** None explicitly detailed in the text.\n**Retrieval Utility:** Optimized for queries on the business impact of attri..."
  },
  {
    "node_id": "0056",
    "title": "三大核心要义：2025年游戏营销者的启示：迈向2026年的关键洞察",
    "page_range": "39-40",
    "summary": "This section answers retrieval queries regarding strategic guidance for game marketing in the 2025–2026 transition period.\n- **Topics & Claims:** Addresses what the three core strategic takeaways are for game marketers. Claims include: (1) steady, systematic growth outperforms aggressive expansion and blind traffic chasing; (2) continuous creative iteration builds more sustainable competitive advantages than simply widening channel portfolios; (3) trust in internal measurement systems drives smart growth, enabling advertisers to compete more agilely and finish 2025 with stronger capabilities than at the year's start.\n- **Entities & Dates:** Identifies game marketers and advertisers as the target audience. Focuses on performance and strategy during 2025, with forward-looking insights for 2026. Cites \"Singular\" as the reporting entity.\n- **Metrics & Concepts:** Highlights strategic concepts and comparative metrics: systematic growth vs. traffic scale, creative iteration vs. channel expansion, measurement system reliability, agile response, and smart/steady growth.\n- **Evidence Types:** Grounds all claims in industry trend analysis from the \"Singular 2025 Quarterly Trend Report.\"\n- **Definitions, Procedures, Tables, Figures:** None explicitly defined, detailed, or presented in this section."
  }
]
